name: Nikkei
summary: Japanese stock markets experienced a significant plunge, with the Nikkei 225 index dropping by 12.4%, marking its worst decline since 1987. The drop was triggered by investors selling off a wide range of shares amid concerns over the U.S. economy. The Dow Jones Industrial Average also fell by 864 points, further exacerbating the global market rout. This decline is considered the largest point drop in the Nikkei's history, surpassing the losses incurred during the 1987 Black Monday crash.

name: Kristen Faulkner
summary: Kristen Faulkner, a former Harvard-Radcliffe cyclist, has made history by winning a gold medal in the women's road cycling event at the 2024 Paris Olympics. Despite initially not being on the Olympic team, Faulkner was selected as a replacement and stunned the cycling world with her victory. The accomplishment marks the first road race Olympic gold medal for the United States women's team in 40 years, and a historic triumph for both Faulkner and her country.

name: Uneven bars 2024 Olympics
summary: Suni Lee has made history as the first American woman to win two Olympic medals in the uneven bars, taking bronze at the 2024 Paris Games. The only American to compete in the event, Lee's bronze medal adds to her impressive Olympic record. Kaylia Nemour of Algeria claimed the gold medal, while Qiu Qiyuan of China secured silver. The uneven bars final featured a competitive lineup, with Lee's bronze securing another medal for the United States in women's gymnastics at the Paris Olympics.
